<p>The Topics section is where you will add links to course materials, 
  organized into <em>topics</em>.<p>

<p>A topic is a group of related course materials. Ultimately, you will 
  assign a topic, or multiple topics, as homework.</p>

<p>To get started creating topics:</p>  
<ol>
  <li>Ensure exercises are hosted on <%= link_to "Quadbase", "http://quadbase.org" %>
     and resources are hosted on <%= link_to "Connexions", "http://cnx.org" %> 
     or other website. </li>
  <li>Organize course materials into topics.</li>
  <li>In the Topics section, click <strong>Add new topic</strong>.</li>
  <li><strong><em>Double click</em></strong> on the topic to add resources 
    and exercises. </li>
  <li>Reveal edit/delete icons by hovering your mouse over the topic name, 
    exercise or resource.</li>
</ol>
